<BaseLayout title="About" description="Support Youth DJs is building shared space around youth DJ culture.">
  <section class="page-head"><div class="page-head-inner"><p class="stamp">About</p><h1>Building shared space around youth DJ culture.</h1><p class="lead">Support Youth DJs is building a shared platform for youth DJ culture by making youth DJs visible, gathering practical knowledge, recognizing people and programs doing the work, connecting related content and resources, and creating a basis for future advocacy.</p></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="section-inner">
    <div class="grid">
      <article class="panel red"><h3>Visibility</h3><p>The directory helps youth DJs under 18 share approved public work, city and state, genres, links, related stories, questions, and learning topics.</p></article>
      <article class="panel"><h3>Knowledge</h3><p>Learning content can draw from bookings, equipment decisions, performance, music preparation, client communication, marketing, pricing, mistakes, recovery, competition, and community.</p></article>
      <article class="panel"><h3>Culture</h3><p>Support Youth DJs can recognize youth DJ movements, programs, local scenes, DJ educators, experienced contributors, community resources, cultural history, and advocacy topics.</p></article>
    </div>
    <ul class="list"><li>Directory participation remains limited to DJs under 18.</li><li>Adults may contribute editorially but are not directory members.</li><li>Ryan is a moderator and contributor. His professional DJ experience is one source of practical knowledge within the larger platform.</li><li>Support Youth DJs does not claim to represent all youth DJs or imply formal partnership without approval.</li></ul>
  </div></section>
</BaseLayout>
